  "dashboardNetCashInfoTitle": "Net cash",
  "dashboardNetCashInfoBody": "Net cash is a signed total for accounts that count toward liquid cash flow: balances on asset accounts (such as checking) are added, and amounts owed on liability accounts (such as credit cards) are subtracted.\n\nAn account is included when “Include in net cash” is turned on for that account. If that was never set, checking and credit card accounts are included by default; savings, investments, loans, and mortgages are not.\n\nFor each included account, Finko uses the balance in your main currency when available; otherwise it uses the balance in that account’s currency.",
